cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.VR, cs.MS, cs.RO 

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on developing a toolkit for novices to interact with virtual objects in a more intuitive and embodied way. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses the visualization and manipulation of complex virtual objects. 
- cs.VR (Virtual Reality) is another likely category as the paper specifically focuses on exploring and manipulating virtual objects in VR. 
- cs.MS (Modeling and Simulation) is a possible category as the paper discusses the use of Composable Shape Primitives to build physical proxy objects. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of Manipulators to enable rich object exploration and manipulation in VR, which could be relevant to robotics research.
